Date: 0/0/1987
Source: Shepherd's Year,  A
Author: HALL
Vol / Page: 81
Edition:
Quote: Some shepherds carry a shearing blade with them so they can shear any woollies they come across, rather than bring them in. Woollies are sheep that have missed shearing at least once, and they may be carrying a lot of excess weight which weakens them.
